# .github/CODEOWNERS
#
# Auto-assigns reviewers when files in these paths are changed in a PR.
# Rules are evaluated bottom-to-top — last matching rule wins.
# GitHub usernames must start with @.
# Org team syntax: @vrworld-exp/team-name (if GitHub Teams are configured)
#
# TODO: Replace @vrworld-exp with the actual founder GitHub username.
#       Verify at: https://github.com/orgs/vrworld-exp/people
#
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ── Default — everything not matched below ────────────────────────────────────
# The founder reviews all PRs by default until the team grows.
*                                   @vrworld-exp

# ── Flutter application code ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
/lib/                               @vrworld-exp
/test/                              @vrworld-exp

# ── Android native module ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Assign to whoever owns the Android/Kotlin native capture module (P3).
# Update this username when the native engineer joins.
/android/                           @vrworld-exp

# ── iOS native module ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Assign to whoever owns the iOS/Swift native capture module (P3).
/ios/                               @vrworld-exp

# ── CI/CD and GitHub configuration ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Highest trust — changes to CI affect all builds.
/.github/                           @vrworld-exp

# ── Dependencies ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# pubspec.yaml changes affect all team members' environments.
/pubspec.yaml                       @vrworld-exp
/pubspec.lock                       @vrworld-exp

# ── Environment and build config ──────────────────────────────────────────────
/Makefile                           @vrworld-exp
/.env.example                       @vrworld-exp
